{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014nGe61sGZybDLiQfg4pAjw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the current `title-extractor.ts`, it already has all the changes from the improvement plan implemented:\n\n1. **Change 1** (bullet filter): Line 182 - `if (/^\\s*[-•*]\\s/.test(text)) return false;` ✓\n2. **Change 2** (section labels): `SECTION_LABELS` set and `isSectionLabel` function, line 184 - `if (isSectionLabel(text)) return false;` ✓\n3. **Change 3** (expanded ingredient detection): Polish units in `MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS`, compact metric and \"to taste\"/\"do smaku\" in `looksLikeIngredient` ✓\n\n\n4. **Change 4** (startsWithNumber hardening): Line 88 - `return /^\\s*(?:[-•*]\\s*)?\\d/.test(line);` ✓\n\nHowever, I notice the improvement plan mentions several \"for the...\" phrases like \"for the sauce\", \"for the filling\", \"for the topping\", \"for the dough\", \"for the crust\", \"for the frosting\", and \"for the glaze\" that should be in `SECTION_LABELS`, but they're missing from the current implementation. The existing code only has the basic section labels, so these additional phrases need to be added to properly catch subsection headers. I'm noticing a discrepancy between what the improvement plan outlined and what's actually implemented. The plan called for adding sub-section keywords like \"for the sauce\" and \"for the filling,\" but those aren't in the current code. More importantly, there's a comment claiming that \"oz\" and \"lb\" are matched using word boundaries instead of being in the MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS array, but I don't see that word-boundary logic actually implemented in the looksLikeIngredient function—it only checks MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS, compact metrics, and \"to taste\" variations. I'm realizing the improvement plan describes changes from iteration 12 to 13, but the current code might already have some of those changes applied. Let me carefully compare what the plan says should change versus what's actually in the file to understand what still needs to be done. I'm noticing that \"oz\" and \"lb\" are actually missing from the current implementation, even though there's a comment acknowledging they need word boundary handling in the `looksLikeIngredient` function—but I don't see that logic actually implemented yet.\n\nThe real issue is that adding \"oz\" and \"lb\" directly to the measurement patterns would create false positives. Words like \"mozzarella\" contain \"oz\" and \"albacore\" contains \"lb\", so the function would incorrectly flag \"mozzarella sticks\" as an ingredient match when it shouldn't.\n\nThe improvement plan suggests putting these back into MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS, but that would actually break the existing tests. The current approach of excluding them makes sense, but it's missing the proper word-boundary matching implementation that would let us safely include them without causing false matches. I'm realizing the plan describes changes from an earlier state, but the current code already has some of those modifications implemented. Let me check what's actually been done versus what still needs to be done by comparing the current title-extractor.ts against the improvement plan. Looking at the git status, the improvement plan directory is showing as untracked, which means these changes might not actually be committed yet—the code I'm seeing could be from a work-in-progress state where the improvements have been applied locally but not yet staged or committed to the branch.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22080,"cache_read_input_tokens":22296,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":22080},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e82029a8-8ec1-4638-ae16-802ee09be476","uuid":"8b2ec4af-73fb-4838-b4c0-8fa4f8c9d332"}
