{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TNuQCTYiemwYK7LthPV8gf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The stop hook is asking me to do a self-review of my changes. Let me review what I changed:\n\n1. In `buildCandidates`, I added `!isSectionLabel(line.text)` checks before creating 2-line and 3-line joins.\n\nLet me think about whether this is the right approach:\n\n**Implementation Completeness:** The fix is real logic, not a placeholder.\n\n**Code Quality:** The fix is minimal - just two added conditions. Is it more complex than needed? Let me think...\n\nThe root cause: `isSectionLabel` only matches exact normalized text. So \"INGREDIENTS MOZZARELLA STICKS\" (a 2-line join) passes because the whole text isn't in SECTION_LABELS.\n\n\nThe approach I went with prevents joins from starting on section label lines, which sidesteps the false positive issue. I considered making `isSectionLabel` check for prefix matches instead, but that risks incorrectly flagging recipe names that happen to start with those words. Same problem if I add the check in `passesHardFilters`. My current solution is cleaner and more targeted—it directly addresses where the problem occurs without introducing new false positives. The code is straightforward and the intent is clear.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":272,"cache_read_input_tokens":60054,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":272},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e82029a8-8ec1-4638-ae16-802ee09be476","uuid":"29f0cc17-c4ca-41e8-bd18-1f2666fc2223"}
