{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01USLjtUBHT362PfMgkGJpmT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-review:\n\n**Implementation Completeness:** Real logic, not a stub. ✓\n\n**Code Quality:** The fix is two added conditions (`!isSectionLabel(line.text)`). One consideration: `isSectionLabel` is called up to twice per line in the join loop, but it's an O(|SECTION_LABELS|) set lookup — negligible. The comment explains the `why` clearly.\n\n**Integration & Refactoring:** Could this be handled differently? The alternative would be extending `isSectionLabel` (or `passesHardFilters`) to also reject text that *starts with* a section label word — but that risks false positives for recipe names like \"Sos Pomidorowy\" (starts with \"sos\" which is in SECTION_LABELS). The join-level guard is more precise: it only prevents joins that *originate* from a section label line, without touching how standalone candidates are evaluated.\n\n**Codebase Consistency:** No other files need updating. The improvement plan Changes 1–4 were already applied to the working tree; my only change is this targeted fix for the remaining test failure.\n\nThe implementation is correct, minimal, and well-commented. No further changes needed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1321,"cache_read_input_tokens":60326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1321},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e82029a8-8ec1-4638-ae16-802ee09be476","uuid":"5cef3f91-1f3b-4cec-a622-a73380263956"}
